{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_83","type":"agent_message","text":"I have the exact lever now: the compose plugin honors `SERVICES_HOST` and uses it before the broken gateway autodetection. I’m patching the Spring AOT triage script to default that variable to `127.0.0.1`, then I’ll rerun the same reproduction to confirm it clears `data-cassandra`."}}
